enhanced vision, enhanced
hearing, healing abilities,

00:21:11.730 --> 00:21:16.110 align:middle line:10%
enhancements to our pituitary
glands, to our pineal glands.

00:21:16.110 --> 00:21:18.424 align:middle line:84%
>>HYPNOTIST: The
glandular system as well?

00:21:18.424 --> 00:21:19.257 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: All of them.

00:21:19.257 --> 00:21:22.840 align:middle line:84%
>>HYPNOTIST: Mhm, make
you efficient machines.

00:21:22.840 --> 00:21:25.090 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: Yes, the better to use.

00:21:25.090 --> 00:21:28.010 align:middle line:90%
>>HYPNOTIST: Better use, oh.

00:21:28.010 --> 00:21:30.180 align:middle line:84%
Did they tell you how they
were going to use you--

00:21:30.180 --> 00:21:30.980 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: No.

00:21:30.980 --> 00:21:32.460 align:middle line:84%
>>HYPNOTIST: --this
efficient machine?

00:21:32.460 --> 00:21:33.260 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: No.

00:21:33.260 --> 00:21:34.390 align:middle line:90%
>>HYPNOTIST: No?

00:21:34.390 --> 00:21:37.350 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: No, they didn't, except
that we were going to be used

00:21:37.350 --> 00:21:38.200 align:middle line:90%
off planet--

00:21:38.200 --> 00:21:40.170 align:middle line:90%
>>HYPNOTIST: Off planet, oh, OK.

00:21:40.170 --> 00:21:43.560 align:middle line:10%
>>RICE: --out of
our solar system.

00:21:43.560 --> 00:21:46.860 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: How many soldiers were
in with you in this training?

00:21:46.860 --> 00:21:51.420 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: The total number
of Earth-provided soldiers

00:21:51.420 --> 00:21:53.940 align:middle line:90%
amounts to about 24,000.

00:21:53.940 --> 00:21:56.151 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: And were they
all different races?

00:21:56.151 --> 00:21:57.150 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: Different races.

00:21:57.150 --> 00:21:58.260 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: And sexes?

00:21:58.260 --> 00:22:00.840 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: Male, female,
different countries.

00:22:00.840 --> 00:22:01.710 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Sizes?

00:22:01.710 --> 00:22:02.830 align:middle line:90%
Tall, short?

00:22:02.830 --> 00:22:03.630 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: Full range.

00:22:03.630 --> 00:22:05.830 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: Any majority
race, Chinese or-- no?

00:22:05.830 --> 00:22:06.630 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: No.

00:22:06.630 --> 00:22:07.671 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Nothing like that.

00:22:07.671 --> 00:22:11.749 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: Only program that
I'm aware of is the MILAB.

00:22:11.749 --> 00:22:13.290 align:middle line:84%
However, other
countries have to have

00:22:13.290 --> 00:22:18.570 align:middle line:84%
their own means of recruiting,
training, selecting.

00:22:18.570 --> 00:22:21.870 align:middle line:84%
So I imagine that other
countries are probably

00:22:21.870 --> 00:22:24.930 align:middle line:84%
either modeled after,
or are copies of,

00:22:24.930 --> 00:22:27.510 align:middle line:84%
or are very similar
to the MILAB program.

00:22:27.510 --> 00:22:28.900 align:middle line:90%
But they do exist.

00:22:28.900 --> 00:22:31.560 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: So how many
people were in your unit?

00:22:31.560 --> 00:22:35.500 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: The smallest
unit size was a squad.

00:22:35.500 --> 00:22:36.300 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: A squad.

00:22:36.300 --> 00:22:39.900 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: And they consisted
of eight to nine individuals.

00:22:39.900 --> 00:22:44.120 align:middle line:84%
And then going out from
there was a platoon.

00:22:44.120 --> 00:22:48.150 align:middle line:84%
And then there were four
platoons per company

00:22:48.150 --> 00:22:51.810 align:middle line:84%
and two to three
companies per battalion.

00:22:51.810 --> 00:22:56.070 align:middle line:84%
It's arranged very similar
to Western military order

00:22:56.070 --> 00:22:56.870 align:middle line:90%
of battle.

00:22:56.870 --> 00:22:57.720 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Right.

00:22:57.720 --> 00:23:01.470 align:middle line:84%
So you're at this
training facility.

00:23:01.470 --> 00:23:04.820 align:middle line:84%
You've now used the
food replicator.

00:23:04.820 --> 00:23:07.830 align:middle line:84%
You've brush your teeth
with this odd nano-thing.

00:23:07.830 --> 00:23:11.354 align:middle line:84%
And now it's the
day of the briefing.

00:23:11.354 --> 00:23:12.520 align:middle line:90%
It's a day and a half later.

00:23:12.520 --> 00:23:14.130 align:middle line:84%
They've told you they're
going to brief you.

00:23:14.130 --> 00:23:15.360 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: Finally, some answers.

00:23:15.360 --> 00:23:15.720 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Right.

00:23:15.720 --> 00:23:17.340 align:middle line:84%
So what happened
at the briefing?

00:23:17.340 --> 00:23:20.070 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: Well, we walked in
and go into the auditorium.

00:23:20.070 --> 00:23:23.220 align:middle line:84%
And all of the other
trainees from my class

00:23:23.220 --> 00:23:26.070 align:middle line:90%
were in there at the same time.

00:23:26.070 --> 00:23:27.900 align:middle line:84%
And they have a
packet waiting for you

00:23:27.900 --> 00:23:31.140 align:middle line:84%
because the auditorium is set
up like a college classroom that

00:23:31.140 --> 00:23:34.830 align:middle line:84%
has one of the foldable desks
alongside of the chair--

00:23:34.830 --> 00:23:36.810 align:middle line:90%
no frills, very basic.

00:23:36.810 --> 00:23:38.970 align:middle line:84%
But on each of the desks
where we were to sit

00:23:38.970 --> 00:23:43.170 align:middle line:84%
was a package waiting for
us that included paperwork

00:23:43.170 --> 00:23:47.400 align:middle line:84%
for signing, more information
on what we were doing.

00:23:47.400 --> 00:23:49.230 align:middle line:90%
They started the briefing.

00:23:49.230 --> 00:23:52.710 align:middle line:84%
The colonel that was in charge
of the training regiment

00:23:52.710 --> 00:23:56.820 align:middle line:84%
came up, and he was German,
and started the briefing

00:23:56.820 --> 00:23:59.790 align:middle line:84%
by telling us that
we were asked here

00:23:59.790 --> 00:24:03.120 align:middle line:84%
because we have special talents
and abilities that they need.

00:24:03.120 --> 00:24:06.120 align:middle line:84%
And what we were
going to be used for

00:24:06.120 --> 00:24:12.390 align:middle line:84%
was the tip of the spear,
patriotism, stars, stripes,

00:24:12.390 --> 00:24:17.430 align:middle line:84%
all the things that appeal to
a young officer that's looking

00:24:17.430 --> 00:24:19.065 align:middle line:90%
to help out his country.

00:24:19.065 --> 00:24:22.320 align:middle line:84%
We were going to be helping
planets defend their planets

00:24:22.320 --> 00:24:24.620 align:middle line:90%
from alien invasion.

00:24:24.620 --> 00:24:25.970 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Really?

00:24:25.970 --> 00:24:27.020 align:middle line:90%
And he was German?

00:24:27.020 --> 00:24:27.620 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: He was German.

00:24:27.620 --> 00:24:28.550 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: A thick German accent?

00:24:28.550 --> 00:24:29.799 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: A thick German accent.

00:24:29.799 --> 00:24:30.770 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Really?

00:24:30.770 --> 00:24:33.140 align:middle line:84%
And he wasn't US
military because this

00:24:33.140 --> 00:24:34.400 align:middle line:90%
isn't the US military.

00:24:34.400 --> 00:24:35.570 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: No, he was not.

00:24:35.570 --> 00:24:37.610 align:middle line:84%
And another thing I
noticed at the briefing

00:24:37.610 --> 00:24:41.800 align:middle line:84%
that a lot of the senior brass
up on stage were also German

00:24:41.800 --> 00:24:44.210 align:middle line:90%
and that there was no--

00:24:44.210 --> 00:24:45.680 align:middle line:90%
and they all had thick accents.

00:24:45.680 --> 00:24:49.970 align:middle line:84%
And there were no Western
or European senior officers

00:24:49.970 --> 00:24:51.016 align:middle line:90%
present on the stage.

00:24:51.016 --> 00:24:51.815 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Wow.

00:24:51.815 --> 00:24:53.770 align:middle line:84%
That probably alerted you
right away there's something--

00:24:53.770 --> 00:24:55.311 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: That was a
big sign at first.

00:24:55.311 --> 00:24:57.630 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: Yeah, that's
very interesting.

00:24:57.630 --> 00:24:59.190 align:middle line:90%
So then what happened?

00:24:59.190 --> 00:25:03.410 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: Well, they talked about
the origins of their program

00:25:03.410 --> 00:25:08.340 align:middle line:84%
in which there was no mention
of alien ETs or assistance

00:25:08.340 --> 00:25:09.140 align:middle line:90%
from aliens.

00:25:09.140 --> 00:25:10.370 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: They took all the
credit for the themselves.

00:25:10.370 --> 00:25:11.390 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: Took all
the credit for it.

00:25:11.390 --> 00:25:12.850 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: I knew you were
going to say that.

00:25:12.850 --> 00:25:14.390 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: Did not
say anything at all

00:25:14.390 --> 00:25:19.100 align:middle line:84%
about a breakaway civilizations,
didn't say anything at all

00:25:19.100 --> 00:25:23.550 align:middle line:84%
about the Earth's cabal,
no mention of that at all.

00:25:23.550 --> 00:25:25.850 align:middle line:84%
They talked about
how much money we'd

00:25:25.850 --> 00:25:28.150 align:middle line:84%
end up with at the end
of our 20 and Back,

00:25:28.150 --> 00:25:30.856 align:middle line:84%
we would get credited
with on our return.

00:25:30.856 --> 00:25:32.480 align:middle line:84%
Of course, they were
going to charge us

00:25:32.480 --> 00:25:35.960 align:middle line:84%
for room and board and
some of the equipment

00:25:35.960 --> 00:25:37.740 align:middle line:84%
that we'd be using
and going through.

00:25:37.740 --> 00:25:39.000 align:middle line:90%
But it was just minor charges.

00:25:39.000 --> 00:25:39.800 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Really?

00:25:39.800 --> 00:25:40.840 align:middle line:90%
They were charging you?

00:25:40.840 --> 00:25:42.090 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: By taking it back out.

00:25:42.090 --> 00:25:43.149 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Oh, my god.

00:25:43.149 --> 00:25:44.690 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: And so at
the end of the day,

00:25:44.690 --> 00:25:47.480 align:middle line:84%
we were supposed to have this
nice, fat, shiny check waiting

00:25:47.480 --> 00:25:48.320 align:middle line:90%
for us.

00:25:48.320 --> 00:25:50.580 align:middle line:84%
There was no mention
of mind wipe.

00:25:50.580 --> 00:25:52.670 align:middle line:84%
There was discussion
about the 20 and Back

00:25:52.670 --> 00:25:55.910 align:middle line:84%
and that when we're finished
with our term of service

00:25:55.910 --> 00:26:00.530 align:middle line:84%
that they had the technological
ability to regress our age

00:26:00.530 --> 00:26:04.470 align:middle line:84%
and then send us back in time
to the point in which we left.

00:26:04.470 --> 00:26:06.230 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: So you're going to be 24.

00:26:06.230 --> 00:26:07.480 align:middle line:90%
And you're going back with a--

00:26:07.480 --> 00:26:09.550 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: A nice
retirement nest egg.

00:26:09.550 --> 00:26:11.770 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: What a great life.

00:26:11.770 --> 00:26:13.320 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: They made
it sound that way.

00:26:13.320 --> 00:26:13.700 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Yeah.

00:26:13.700 --> 00:26:16.075 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: Yeah, they didn't
mention anything about the mind

00:26:16.075 --> 00:26:16.928 align:middle line:90%
wipes or--

00:26:16.928 --> 00:26:19.302 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: What did you do with
your money when you got back?

00:26:19.302 --> 00:26:22.084 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: [LAUGHS] What money?

00:26:22.084 --> 00:26:24.500 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: You mean the Germans
weren't telling you the truth?

00:26:24.500 --> 00:26:25.730 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: They weren't
telling us the truth.

00:26:25.730 --> 00:26:26.530 align:middle line:90%
Imagine that.

00:26:26.530 --> 00:26:28.730 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: I can't
even believe that.

00:26:28.730 --> 00:26:31.250 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: The history
that they presented in

00:26:31.250 --> 00:26:34.265 align:middle line:90%
that briefing was very spotty.

00:26:34.265 --> 00:26:38.390 align:middle line:84%
It did not have much in
the way of information.

00:26:38.390 --> 00:26:40.280 align:middle line:84%
The information
that they put forth

00:26:40.280 --> 00:26:43.370 align:middle line:84%
was more of the
propaganda side of it,

00:26:43.370 --> 00:26:46.220 align:middle line:84%
of how great it was that we
were going to be helping out,

00:26:46.220 --> 00:26:48.890 align:middle line:84%
and how much benefit
we'd be providing

00:26:48.890 --> 00:26:55.470 align:middle line:84%
to not only our own families and
country but to the human race.

00:26:55.470 --> 00:26:57.160 align:middle line:90%
It was a load of BS.

00:26:57.160 --> 00:27:00.110 align:middle line:84%
It was the propaganda
lies that they use

00:27:00.110 --> 00:27:01.402 align:middle line:90%
to try and get people on board.

00:27:01.402 --> 00:27:02.201 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Right.

00:27:02.201 --> 00:27:03.002 align:middle line:90%
And it worked.

00:27:03.002 --> 00:27:03.917 align:middle line:90%
>>RICE: And it worked.

00:27:03.917 --> 00:27:04.790 align:middle line:90%
Of course, it did.

00:27:04.790 --> 00:27:07.950 align:middle line:84%
There was no mention of what
they were going to do later

00:27:07.950 --> 00:27:10.920 align:middle line:90%
at the end of our training.

00:27:10.920 --> 00:27:13.230 align:middle line:84%
Similar to Cortes
burning his ships,

00:27:13.230 --> 00:27:16.500 align:middle line:84%
they notified our families
that we had died in action.

00:27:16.500 --> 00:27:20.670 align:middle line:84%
So if we wanted to,
we couldn't go back

00:27:20.670 --> 00:27:23.190 align:middle line:84%
because all our families
thought we were dead.

00:27:23.190 --> 00:27:27.600 align:middle line:84%
They either provided no
body, in which it was just

00:27:27.600 --> 00:27:31.170 align:middle line:84%
an empty casket, or they
provided a clone in the cases.

00:27:31.170 --> 00:27:33.810 align:middle line:84%
And they provided some
clones so that people

00:27:33.810 --> 00:27:36.450 align:middle line:84%
would have a body that looked
just like their loved one

00:27:36.450 --> 00:27:37.640 align:middle line:90%
to bury.

00:27:37.640 --> 00:27:38.440 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Wow.

00:27:38.440 --> 00:27:40.150 align:middle line:84%
>>RICE: And so there
was no turning back.

00:27:40.150 --> 00:27:41.230 align:middle line:90%
They didn't tell us that.

00:27:41.230 --> 00:27:43.110 align:middle line:84%
They didn't say
anything about that.

00:27:43.110 --> 00:27:46.160 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:27:46.160 --> 00:28:07.680 align:middle line:90%